    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix off-by-one error in PDU size calculation causing buffer overflow\n\n### Summary\nThe PDU size calculation in multiple packing functions was incorrectly adding only 1 byte instead of 2 bytes for the header fields. This caused downstream unpacking functions to read beyond buffer boundaries, leading to potential segfaults or corrupted data processing.\n\nThe issue manifests when processing UL config requests with multiple PDUs, where the unpacking function attempts to read past the allocated buffer end.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/nfapi/src/nfapi_p7.c`: Corrected PDU size calculation in 5 packing functions:\n  * `pack_ul_config_request_body_value` \n  * `pack_dl_config_request_body_value`\n  * `pack_lbt_dl_config_request_body_value` \n  * `pack_hi_dci0_request_body_value`\n  * `pack_lbt_dl_config_indication_value`\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder heavy load with multiple PDU configurations, the system experiences segfaults in the unpacking routines. Memory debugging tools show reads past allocated buffer boundaries when processing unpacked PDU data.\n"
}